  m_Name: StoryCard_12_EddaGrandfather
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Hollowfen.Data.StoryCardData
  _id: edda_grandfather
  _act: Act II
  _scene: Scene 5
  _title: Brightspore at the Bedside
  _subtitle: A real person, saved.
  _body: "Edda's grandfather had not eaten a full bowl in three weeks. The Brightspore
    tonic \u2014 bitter, faintly luminous, found at the foot of one specific birch
    \u2014 sets him up against his pillows by the second evening. He says the soup
    tastes like when he was small. Edda doesn't know what to do with that, and so
    she stands at the door with a strangely heavy face."
  _wrenNote: Edda told me her grandfather ate today, the whole bowl. She said it
    like she was reporting weather. Then she walked away. I had to put my forehead
    against the doorframe.
  _beats:
  - Edda's grandfather recovers thanks to a Brightspore tonic.
  - The village sees a foraged mushroom save a life.
  - Edda speaks her first full sentence to Wren.
  _image: {fileID: 21300000, guid: eea468fe5a83d49e0b94c3999e71c7a3, type: 3}
  _unlockAt: 11
  _questId: edsGrandfather
  _displayNameId: story.edda_grandfather.title
